8. Thus it is clear from the aforesaid judgment that the guidelines laid down for the Magistrate for enlarging an accused on bail also applies to the Sessions Court as well as to the High Court in matters of enlargement of an accused on bail. However, so far as cancellation of bail is concerned the same stands on different footing altogether. It has been held by the Apex Court that granting of bail is one thing and cancellation thereof is quite another. Supreme Court in 

Dolat Ram and Ors. v. State of Haryana
 in paragraph 4 thereof has observed thus;

9. It is also been held by the Apex Court in 
Gudikanti Narasimhulu and Ors. v. Public Prosecutor, High
 Court of Andhra Pradesh in paragraph 7, 8 and 9 as follows;
